						               													<description>True Crime Legends is a gangster themed card game for 3-5 players. It takes around an hour to play. Players will lead a syndicate competing to control the lucrative and dangerous markets of the underworld. Invest in assets, smuggle, bribe, murder, steal and hire legendary gangsters from a deck of the most iconic criminals of the past century, each with unique stats and abilities. Ruthlessly rise above your rivals to be crowned the boss of bosses.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(website)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players start with one boss card, but there is a public marketplace that allows players to fill out a tableau (their syndicate) by draft-purchasing up to 3 extra *historical* gangsters, 4 assets (usually venues associated with crime) and 4 upgrades (eg drug boats, evidence, guns, armor).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The tableau allows each gangster to be lined up with an Asset and an Upgrade which increase the gangster's abilities.&amp;#10;The players will take it in turn to activate each gangster, with various abilities including earning money, stealing money, attacking other gangsters, stealing other gangsters, destroying Assets/Upgrades and attempting a narcotics shipment. The success of these actions depends on a dice roll, but increasing the gangsters' abilities increases their chance of success. If they do not succeed, a gangster they have targeted will usually have an ability that allows retaliation.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Some of the Assets (locations) give income at the end of each round, if they still have a gangster assigned to them.&amp;#10;At the end of four rounds, the player with the most money is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(NB this is based on the 2018 version of the game)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
